<alert xmlns="urn:oasis:names:tc:emergency:cap:1.2">
    <identifier>{UUID}</identifier>
    <sender>{OriginatingAgencyIdentifier}</sender>
    <sent>{ISO8601_Timestamp}</sent>
    <status>Actual</status> <!-- Actual | Exercise | System | Test | Draft -->
    <msgType>Alert</msgType> <!-- Alert | Update | Cancel | Ack | Error -->
    <source>{SourceSystemOrFeed}</source>
    <scope>Public</scope> <!-- Public | Restricted | Private -->

    <info>
        <category>{Geo | Met | Safety | Security | Rescue | Fire | Health | Env | Transport | Infra | CBRNE | Other}</category>
        <event>{EventName}</event>
        <responseType>{Shelter | Evacuate | Prepare | Execute | Avoid | Monitor | Assess | None}</responseType>
        <urgency>{Immediate | Expected | Future | Past | Unknown}</urgency>
        <severity>{Extreme | Severe | Moderate | Minor | Unknown}</severity>
        <certainty>{Observed | Likely | Possible | Unlikely | Unknown}</certainty>

        <senderName>{AgencyName}</senderName>
        <headline>{ShortHeadline}</headline>
        <description>{FullEventDescription}</description>
        <instruction>{PublicInstructions}</instruction>

        <area>
            <areaDesc>{GeographicDescription}</areaDesc>
            <polygon>{lat,lon lat,lon lat,lon}</polygon> <!-- optional -->
            <circle>{lat,lon radius}</circle> <!-- optional -->
            <geocode>
                <valueName>SAME</valueName>
                <value>{FIPS_Code}</value>
            </geocode>
        </area>

        <parameter>
            <valueName>incidentID</valueName>
            <value>{InternalIncidentIdentifier}</value>
        </parameter>

        <parameter>
            <valueName>sourceFeed</valueName>
            <value>{FeedNameOrURL}</value>
        </parameter>
    </info>
</alert>


1. Required Fields for Valid CAP
identifier
sender
sent
status
msgType
scope
At least one <info> block
Ingestion layer should reject or quarantine alerts missing these.
2. Fields Your System Should Extract Immediately
Severity / Urgency / Certainty → feeds your context‑gradient engine
Event → maps to your disaster‑chain node
Area → geospatial normalization
Parameters → lineage anchors, feed metadata, incident correlation
3. Fields to Ignore or Down‑weight
CAP often contains:
vague descriptions
inconsistent geocodes
non‑standard parameter names
Normalization layer should sanitize these.
